			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>
We are looking for a dynamic Data Scientist to join our Lean Product Management team. The Data Scientist will work closely with the VP of Programme Management and VP of Product Management to analyse an amazing wealth of data to improve every aspect of our service.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate will combine a deep passion for innovative use of data in a real world business context with a high degree of pragmatism.</p>
<p>
<strong>Essential Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>
Work with the product and business teams to identify opportunities to use data to improve Workshare&rsquo;s existing product offerings, develop new products and services, as well as generally understanding Workshare&rsquo;s business and the social collaboration space better.</li>
<li>
Help define appropriate metrics and models to ensure that Workshare is able to understand how the Company products and services are performing, and advise on strategies for collecting appropriate data.</li>
<li>
Work with the Programme Management team to develop and maintain data products and tools for use across the broader company.</li>
<li>
Build models based on our data to better understand current trends and predict the likely effects of business decisions.</li>
<li>
Identify cases where there is value in collecting new types of data and work with third parties and members of the Workshare team to complete the data acquisition process.</li>
<li>
Advise the development team on the technical implementation of any products which make heavy use of data or data analysis technology.</li>
</ol>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>
A highly analytical approach. Ability to express business and product questions in precise terms and explore hypotheses systematically and scientifically.</li>
<li>
A background in data modelling, statistics, business intelligence, funnel/cohort analysis, etc. in a real-world business environment. The successful candidate will ideally have experience in a similar role.</li>
<li>
The ability to get things done and vigorously apply the 80/20 rule.</li>
<li>
Exceptional communication skills, whether with both technical and non-technical team members.</li>
<li>
A strong business sense and appreciation of how the work of the Data Scientist fits into the decision making process.</li>
<li>
Sufficient experience with software development to automate routine tasks and perform analysis at scale (MySQL, RoR, JS, R, MixPanel, Google Analytics, ..).</li>
<li>
University degree in mathematics or computer science (or other quantitative subjects)</li>
</ol>
]]></description>
