			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>We are</strong><br />
Workshare is a next-generation enterprise collaboration platform that facilitates multi-party collaboration across departments, between offices, clients and among partners. Workshare solutions are used by individuals and organizations of all sizes to increase productivity and protect confidential information. Our mission is to provide a fully integrated, highly secure, enterprise-grade file sharing, collaboration and social platform across mobile, web and desktop.</p>
<p>
<strong>We seek</strong><br />
Working in our HQ in East London, as a SysAdmin/DevOps engineer, you will be part of a talented agile development team building the Workshare platform and will report to the Senior Architect.</p>
<p>
<strong>Our tech stack</strong><br />
AWS, Ubuntu, Gentoo, Vagrant, Chef, Puppet, Ruby, Rails, Node.js, MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis, HAProxy, Apache, nginx, Tomcat, Java, Spring, Hibernate, Hazelcast, Solr, git, Maven, JavaScript, .NET, Selenium, Jenkins, Jira, Artifactory, VirtualBox, CloudSigma, Sonar, Linux, Mac OS X, Windows, iOS and Android devices.</p>
<p>
<strong>You are</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
An exceptional system administrator engineer, you can both support agile software development teams and follow production environments.</li>
<li>
A strong believer and committed practitioner of agile and lean methodologies, you understand the principles behind them beyond the buzzwords.</li>
<li>
Capable of troubleshooting production environments problems to the finest detail and collaborate closely with QA and developers for resolution.</li>
<li>
Deeply rooted in the DevOps culture, you do get &quot;infrastructure as code&quot;.</li>
<li>
A relentless automator and fond of anything continuous: integration, deployment and delivery, you know how to make the life the members of your team better through automation of every possible repeatable task.</li>
<li>
Skilled in cloud and virtualization, you understand IaaS, PaaS and SaaS and are able to setup private and public cloud infrastructures as well as repeatable virtualized environments for testing and deployment.</li>
<li>
Experienced in high availability, security and scaling technologies for the internet, you can setup operations to guarantee production SLAs.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>You have</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Extensive experience in network, database and operating systems.</li>
<li>
Proven skills in Unix shell scripting.</li>
<li>
Production experience with public clouds like AWS, Rackspace or similar.</li>
<li>
Proven skills in automated tools for system provisioning like Chef, Puppet and Vagrant for local testing environment setups.</li>
<li>
Administered web applications (Java, Rails, .NET) and used monitoring software (Nagios, Zabbix) or cloud services (New Relic, Airbrake, SendGrid, MixPanel).</li>
<li>
Setup and supported software factories using Jira, Jenkins, Maven and git, rake, bundler.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>You should ideally have</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
BSc or Msc in Computer Science from a top university.</li>
<li>
Setup a private cloud infrastructure using CloudStack, OpenStack or similar and have strong knowledge of provisioning and packaging tools.</li>
<li>
Production support experience with NoSQL databases like MongoDB, Redis, OrientDB, Cassandra.</li>
<li>
Setup usage metrics collection system and related reporting and visualization to support business validation of new features.</li>
</ul>
